30/04/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police on Thursday (29 April) detained Ljupco Popovski, state secretary at the defence ministry, amid allegations of bribe-taking. 
He reportedly had demanded 15,000 euros in return for arranging a speedier land sale. 
Popovski is a senior official in the ruling SDSM party.
In other news, UNMIK announced Thursday that it has extradited two former commanders of the disbanded National Liberation Army to Macedonia. 
Avdyl Jakupi, known as Cakala, and Xhemail Hyseni, known as Jamie Shea, are accused of terrorism and looting. 
(Utrinski Vesnik -30/04/04; Makfax - 29/04/04)
